---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { Icon } from 'astro-icon/components';

const stories = [
  {
    id: 'three-capybaras-and-a-very-bad-pull',
    title: 'Three Capybaras and a Very Bad Pull',
    lead: 'A Midnight run turns from clean execution into glorious nonsense, and somehow forges a party that should not work but absolutely does.',
    imageSrc: '/images/lore/three-capybaras-and-a-very-bad-pull.png',
    imageAlt: 'Jethro and Doug cuddled beside a fireplace with spirit capybara Gortham glowing between them.',
    characters: ['Doug', 'Jethro', 'Gortham'],
    paragraphs: [
      "Doug met Jethro the way most Mythic+ disasters begin - everything was going perfectly until it suddenly wasn't.",
      'It was a Midnight dungeon, all violet shadows and suspiciously glowing objects. Doug was doing his job the right way: controlled pulls, steady footing, no nonsense. The kind of run that finishes clean, quiet, and uneventful.',
      'Then Jethro happened.',
      "He didn't ease into chaos - he committed to it. One moment the dungeon was under control, the next he had somehow collected half the room, a patrol, and something that probably wasn't even supposed to be active yet. The pull collapsed onto Doug like a tidal wave of bad decisions.",
      'They wiped. Hard.',
      'And then they did it again.',
      'But somewhere between the second wipe and the third attempt, something strange started to work. Doug adapted, planting himself like an anchor while Jethro\'s unpredictable movement began funneling enemies back toward him. What should have been pure disaster turned into something... functional.',
      'Messy. Loud. Completely ill-advised.',
      'But functional.',
      "By the end of the run, the group was exhausted, confused, and somehow victorious. Doug had no logical reason to tolerate Jethro's chaos - but he didn't leave. And Jethro, for all his recklessness, kept circling back like he belonged there.",
      'They started running together after that.',
      "Doug brought stability. Jethro brought momentum. Neither would admit it, but they balanced each other in a way that made no sense on paper and perfect sense in practice.",
      'Gortham came later, during a run that felt wrong from the start.',
      'The dungeon was too quiet. Pulls were missing. The air had that subtle, glitchy stillness that meant something in reality had slipped a little out of place. Naturally, this is when Jethro decided to investigate.',
      'The moment he did, the world stuttered.',
      'Light warped. Shadows bent. And in the middle of it all, something small appeared.',
      'A tiny capybara shape, glowing in soft blues and purples, like it was not fully anchored to the same world as everything else.',
      'Gortham.',
      'He did not attack. Did not run. Just hovered there, uncertain, as if waiting to see what would happen next.',
      'Jethro approached first, curious as ever. Doug followed more cautiously, watching, thinking. But when the little spirit drifted closer and settled between them - quiet, trusting - it stopped being a question.',
      'They did not leave him behind.',
      'The dungeon reset itself like nothing had happened. Enemies returned. The run continued.',
      'But Gortham stayed.',
      'He did not fight or pull or do anything useful in the traditional sense. He just... existed. A soft, glowing presence that followed them from room to room, occasionally bumping into Doug or drifting lazily around Jethro\'s endless movement.',
      'And somehow, it felt right.',
      'Since then, the three of them have been inseparable.',
      'Doug still anchors every fight. Jethro still turns every pull into a questionable life choice. And Gortham floats between them, a small piece of something unexplainable that neither of them would ever give up.',
      'It should not work.',
      'But it does.'
    ]
  },
  {
    id: 'the-hidden-lodge-a-safe-space-away-from-the-floor',
    title: 'The Hidden Lodge: A Safe Space Away From the Floor',
    lead: 'Some guilds are forged in conquest. This one was forged in survival, shared disbelief, and one unforgettable horizontal shot-caller.',
    imageSrc: '/images/lore/the-hidden-lodge-a-safe-space-away-from-the-floor.png',
    imageAlt: 'An enraged raid leader points at camera while yelling about HR, with a wipe screen visible behind her.',
    characters: ['The Survivors', 'HR (The Dog)', 'The Hidden Lodge'],
    paragraphs: [
      "Legends say The Hidden Lodge wasn't founded-it escaped into existence. Once upon a very unfortunate raid tier, a group of hopeful adventurers answered the call of a guild that promised glory, progression, and elite leadership.",
      "What they got instead was a raid leader who treated the floor like a second home. She would charge confidently into battle, immediately perish, and then begin issuing commands with absolute authority from her now-horizontal command center. DEFENSIVES! she would scream, moments after everyone had already used them, as the raid collectively burned in ways both magical and emotional. Her parses hovered bravely in the single digits, which she described as misunderstood excellence, and she coached others relentlessly despite having the survivability of a decorative candle.",
      "Between pulls, things only got stranger. Her ever-present, deeply concerned dog-introduced to the raid as HR-sat silently in the background of every call, carrying the haunted expression of a creature that had witnessed too many performance reviews. Meanwhile, she frequently paused raid to announce that various guild members had fallen in love with her, a conclusion she reached after aggressively flirting with anything capable of responding in Discord. The volume was always at maximum, the emotions were always dialed to eleven, and the rest of the raid slowly bonded-not over loot, not over success, but over shared confusion and secondhand embarrassment.",
      "Eventually, one by one, then in groups, then in what could only be described as a mass exodus disguised as taking a break, the survivors slipped away. They found each other again later, drawn together by a strange, unspoken understanding-the kind only forged in the fires of chaotic raid nights and unsolicited life coaching from someone spectating their own mistakes. And there, in the quiet aftermath, they formed The Hidden Lodge: a guild built not on parses or perfection, but on camaraderie, mild PTSD, and the revolutionary idea that the raid leader should maybe, occasionally... still be alive."
    ]
  }
];

const featuredStoryId = 'the-hidden-lodge-a-safe-space-away-from-the-floor';
const orderedStories = [...stories].sort((a, b) => {
  if (a.id === featuredStoryId) return -1;
  if (b.id === featuredStoryId) return 1;
  return 0;
});

const selectedStoryId = Astro.url.searchParams.get('story');
const selectedStory = stories.find((story) => story.id === selectedStoryId);
const usesAsideStoryImage = selectedStory?.id === featuredStoryId;
const usesTopStoryImage = Boolean(selectedStory) && !usesAsideStoryImage;
---

<Layout title="The Hidden Lodge | Lore" description="Fictional stories from The Hidden Lodge featuring guild characters and dungeon chaos.">
  <section class="hero" aria-labelledby="lore-title">
    <p class="eyebrow">Guild Lore Archive</p>
    <h1 id="lore-title">Stories from the Lodge</h1>
    <p class="intro">
      Fictional (maybe?) tales inspired by raid nights, Mythic+ disasters, and the strange chemistry that keeps this guild together.
    </p>
  </section>

  <div id="lightbox" class="lightbox" role="dialog" aria-modal="true" aria-label="Story image full size" hidden>
    <button class="lightbox-close" id="lightbox-close" aria-label="Close">&times;</button>
    <img id="lightbox-img" src="" alt="" />
  </div>

  {
    !selectedStory && (
      <section class="story-picker" aria-labelledby="story-picker-title">
        <div class="story-picker-head">
          <h2 id="story-picker-title">Choose Your Story</h2>
          <p>Pick a tale to open the full archive entry.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="story-grid" role="list">
          {
            orderedStories.map((story) => (
              <article class="story-preview" role="listitem">
                <a class="preview-image-link" href={`/lore?story=${story.id}`} aria-label={`Read story: ${story.title}`}>
                  <img class="preview-image" src={story.imageSrc} alt={story.imageAlt} loading="lazy" />
                </a>
                <div class="preview-content">
                  <h3>
                    <a class="story-title-link" href={`/lore?story=${story.id}`}>{story.title}</a>
                  </h3>
                  <p>{story.lead}</p>
                  <div class="chips" aria-label="Featured characters">
                    {
                      story.characters.map((name) => (
                        <span class="chip">
                          <Icon name="lucide:user-round" aria-hidden="true" />
                          {name}
                        </span>
                      ))
                    }
                  </div>
                  <a class="open-story" href={`/lore?story=${story.id}`}>
                    <Icon name="lucide:book-open-text" aria-hidden="true" />
                    Read Story
                  </a>
                </div>
              </article>
            ))
          }
        </div>
      </section>
    )
  }

  {
    selectedStory && (
      <section class="stories" aria-label="Selected lore story">
        <div class="story-toolbar">
          <a class="back-to-list" href="/lore">
            <Icon name="lucide:arrow-left" aria-hidden="true" />
            Back to story list
          </a>

          <form class="story-switcher" method="get" action="/lore">
            <label for="story-select">Jump to story</label>
            <select id="story-select" name="story" onchange="this.form.submit()">
              {
                orderedStories.map((story) => (
                  <option value={story.id} selected={story.id === selectedStory.id}>
                    {story.title}
                  </option>
                ))
              }
            </select>
            <noscript>
              <button type="submit">Go</button>
            </noscript>
          </form>
        </div>

        <article class:list={["story-card", usesAsideStoryImage && 'story-card--floating-image']} id={selectedStory.id}>
          <header class="story-head">
            <h2>{selectedStory.title}</h2>
            <p>{selectedStory.lead}</p>
            <div class="chips" aria-label="Featured characters">
              {
                selectedStory.characters.map((name) => (
                  <span class="chip">
                    <Icon name="lucide:user-round" aria-hidden="true" />
                    {name}
                  </span>
                ))
              }
            </div>
          </header>

          <div class:list={["story-body", usesAsideStoryImage && 'story-body--with-aside-image']}>
            {
              usesTopStoryImage && (
                <button
                  class="story-image-button"
                  data-lightbox-src={selectedStory.imageSrc}
                  data-lightbox-alt={selectedStory.imageAlt}
                  aria-label={`View full image for ${selectedStory.title}`}
                  type="button"
                >
                  <img class="story-image" src={selectedStory.imageSrc} alt={selectedStory.imageAlt} loading="lazy" />
                </button>
              )
            }
            {
              usesAsideStoryImage && (
                <button
                  class="story-image-button story-image-button--aside"
                  data-lightbox-src={selectedStory.imageSrc}
                  data-lightbox-alt={selectedStory.imageAlt}
                  aria-label={`View full image for ${selectedStory.title}`}
                  type="button"
                >
                  <img
                    class="story-image story-image--aside"
                    src={selectedStory.imageSrc}
                    alt={selectedStory.imageAlt}
                    loading="lazy"
                  />
                </button>
              )
            }
            {
              selectedStory.paragraphs.map((paragraph) => (
                <p>{paragraph}</p>
              ))
            }
          </div>
        </article>
      </section>
    )
  }

  <script>
    const lightbox = document.getElementById('lightbox');
    const lightboxImg = document.getElementById('lightbox-img');
    const closeBtn = document.getElementById('lightbox-close');

    function openLightbox(src: string, alt: string) {
      if (!(lightbox instanceof HTMLElement) || !(lightboxImg instanceof HTMLImageElement)) return;
      lightboxImg.src = src;
      lightboxImg.alt = alt;
      lightbox.hidden = false;
      lightbox.focus();
      document.body.style.overflow = 'hidden';
    }

    function closeLightbox() {
      if (!(lightbox instanceof HTMLElement) || !(lightboxImg instanceof HTMLImageElement)) return;
      lightbox.hidden = true;
      lightboxImg.src = '';
      lightboxImg.alt = '';
      document.body.style.overflow = '';
    }

    document.querySelectorAll('[data-lightbox-src]').forEach((button) => {
      button.addEventListener('click', () => {
        if (!(button instanceof HTMLElement)) return;
        openLightbox(button.dataset.lightboxSrc ?? '', button.dataset.lightboxAlt ?? '');
      });
    });

    if (closeBtn) closeBtn.addEventListener('click', closeLightbox);

    if (lightbox) {
      lightbox.addEventListener('click', (event) => {
        if (event.target === lightbox) closeLightbox();
      });
    }

    document.addEventListener('keydown', (event) => {
      if (event.key === 'Escape' && lightbox instanceof HTMLElement && !lightbox.hidden) {
        closeLightbox();
      }
    });
  </script>
</Layout>

<style>
  .hero {
    border: 1px solid rgba(214, 176, 106, 0.35);
    border-radius: 0.85rem;
    padding: 1.15rem 1.15rem 1.2rem;
    background:
      linear-gradient(165deg, rgba(214, 176, 106, 0.1), transparent 52%),
      rgba(10, 20, 30, 0.8);
    box-shadow: 0 15px 28px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.22);
  }

  .eyebrow {
    margin: 0;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: #e8c88c;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .hero h1 {
    margin: 0.2rem 0 0;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 3.3vw, 3rem);
    color: #f0d7a7;
    text-shadow: 0 0 16px rgba(214, 176, 106, 0.2);
  }

  .intro {
    margin: 0.7rem 0 0;
    max-width: 75ch;
    color: #d6e0e7;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }

  .story-picker {
    margin-top: 1.2rem;
    border: 1px solid rgba(214, 176, 106, 0.32);
    border-radius: 0.85rem;
    padding: 0.9rem;
    background:
      linear-gradient(155deg, rgba(214, 176, 106, 0.08), transparent 55%),
      rgba(8, 17, 27, 0.78);
    box-shadow: 0 12px 22px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.25);
  }

  .story-picker-head h2 {
    margin: 0;
    color: #f1d9a9;
    font-size: clamp(1.2rem, 2vw, 1.7rem);
  }

  .story-picker-head p {
    margin: 0.35rem 0 0;
    color: #d8e2e8;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .story-grid {
    margin-top: 0.8rem;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr));
  }

  .story-preview {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-rows: auto 1fr;
    border: 1px solid rgba(214, 176, 106, 0.28);
    border-radius: 0.7rem;
    overflow: hidden;
    background: rgba(10, 20, 31, 0.82);
  }

  .preview-image {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    aspect-ratio: 16 / 10;
    object-fit: cover;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(214, 176, 106, 0.22);
    background: rgba(8, 16, 24, 0.9);
  }

  .preview-image-link {
    display: block;
  }

  .preview-image-link:hover .preview-image,
  .preview-image-link:focus-visible .preview-image {
    filter: brightness(1.06);
  }

  .preview-content {
    padding: 0.75rem;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.6rem;
    align-content: stretch;
    grid-template-rows: auto 1fr auto auto;
  }

  .preview-content h3 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 1.12rem;
    color: #f1d9a9;
  }

  .story-title-link {
    color: inherit;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .story-title-link:hover,
  .story-title-link:focus-visible {
    color: #f6e4c2;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 0.18rem;
  }

  .preview-content p {
    margin: 0;
    color: #d6e0e7;
    line-height: 1.45;
    font-size: 0.98rem;
  }

  .open-story {
    justify-self: start;
    align-self: start;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.45rem;
    border: 1px solid rgba(214, 176, 106, 0.4);
    border-radius: 999px;
    padding: 0.62rem 1.15rem;
    color: #1b1408;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #f2d9aa, #dcb06a);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 18px rgba(214, 176, 106, 0.34);
    transition: transform 120ms ease, box-shadow 120ms ease, filter 120ms ease;
  }

  .open-story:hover,
  .open-story:focus-visible {
    filter: brightness(1.05);
    transform: translateY(-1px);
    box-shadow: 0 11px 20px rgba(214, 176, 106, 0.42);
  }

  .open-story :global(svg) {
    width: 1.05rem;
    height: 1.05rem;
  }

  .stories {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .story-toolbar {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    border: 1px solid rgba(214, 176, 106, 0.3);
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    padding: 0.7rem 0.8rem;
    background:
      linear-gradient(150deg, rgba(214, 176, 106, 0.08), transparent 52%),
      rgba(9, 18, 28, 0.75);
  }

  .back-to-list {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.4rem;
    font-size: 0.97rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #f0d7a7;
  }

  .back-to-list:hover,
  .back-to-list:focus-visible {
    color: #f7e5c2;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 0.18rem;
  }

  .back-to-list :global(svg) {
    width: 0.95rem;
    height: 0.95rem;
  }

  .story-switcher {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .story-switcher label {
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: #d5e0e7;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .story-switcher select {
    min-width: 15rem;
    border: 1px solid rgba(214, 176, 106, 0.38);
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    background: rgba(8, 16, 24, 0.92);
    color: #f0e0bd;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    padding: 0.38rem 0.5rem;
  }

  .story-switcher button {
    border: 1px solid rgba(214, 176, 106, 0.45);
    border-radius: 0.45rem;
    background: rgba(214, 176, 106, 0.14);
    color: #f3dfb6;
    padding: 0.3rem 0.55rem;
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .story-card {
    border: 1px solid rgba(214, 176, 106, 0.38);
    border-radius: 0.85rem;
    overflow: hidden;
    background: rgba(9, 18, 28, 0.8);
    box-shadow: 0 14px 28px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.26);
    scroll-margin-top: 6.5rem;
  }

  .story-head {
    padding: 1rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(214, 176, 106, 0.24);
    background:
      linear-gradient(160deg, rgba(214, 176, 106, 0.12), transparent 50%),
      rgba(10, 20, 30, 0.86);
  }

  .story-head h2 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: clamp(1.35rem, 2.4vw, 2rem);
    color: #f1d9a9;
  }

  .story-head p {
    margin: 0.6rem 0 0;
    color: #dae4ea;
    max-width: 72ch;
    font-size: 1.03rem;
  }

  .story-image {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    max-height: none;
    object-fit: contain;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(214, 176, 106, 0.24);
    background: rgba(8, 16, 24, 0.9);
  }

  .story-image-button {
    all: unset;
    display: block;
    cursor: zoom-in;
  }

  .story-image-button:focus-visible {
    outline: 2px solid #e4c27a;
    outline-offset: 3px;
  }

  .story-image-button:hover .story-image,
  .story-image-button:focus-visible .story-image {
    filter: brightness(1.04);
  }

  .story-image-button--aside {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 22rem;
  }

  .story-image--aside {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 22rem;
    margin: 0;
    border: 1px solid rgba(214, 176, 106, 0.24);
    border-radius: 0.7rem;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .chips {
    margin-top: 0.8rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.45rem;
  }

  .chip {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.38rem;
    border: 1px solid rgba(214, 176, 106, 0.42);
    border-radius: 999px;
    padding: 0.3rem 0.62rem;
    color: #f1ddb4;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    background: rgba(214, 176, 106, 0.1);
  }

  .chip :global(svg) {
    width: 0.82rem;
    height: 0.82rem;
  }

  .story-body {
    padding: 1rem;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .story-body--with-aside-image {
    grid-template-columns: minmax(16rem, 22rem) minmax(0, 1fr);
    align-items: start;
    column-gap: 1rem;
  }

  .story-body--with-aside-image .story-image--aside {
    grid-column: 1;
    grid-row: 1 / span 4;
    position: sticky;
    top: 5.5rem;
  }

  .story-body--with-aside-image .story-image-button--aside {
    grid-column: 1;
    grid-row: 1 / span 4;
    position: sticky;
    top: 5.5rem;
  }

  .story-body--with-aside-image p {
    grid-column: 2;
  }

  .story-body p {
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.65;
    font-size: 1.02rem;
    color: #d4dfe6;
  }

  .lightbox {
    position: fixed;
    inset: 0;
    z-index: 1000;
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.88);
    display: grid;
    place-items: center;
  }

  .lightbox[hidden] {
    display: none;
  }

  .lightbox img {
    max-width: min(92vw, 1000px);
    max-height: 92vh;
    border-radius: 0.6rem;
    border: 1px solid rgba(214, 176, 106, 0.5);
    box-shadow: 0 24px 64px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7);
    object-fit: contain;
  }

  .lightbox-close {
    position: absolute;
    top: 1.25rem;
    right: 1.5rem;
    background: transparent;
    border: 1px solid rgba(214, 176, 106, 0.45);
    border-radius: 50%;
    color: #e4c27a;
    font-size: 1.6rem;
    line-height: 1;
    width: 2.4rem;
    height: 2.4rem;
    display: grid;
    place-items: center;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: background 0.15s;
  }

  .lightbox-close:hover,
  .lightbox-close:focus-visible {
    background: rgba(214, 176, 106, 0.18);
  }

  @media (max-width: 700px) {
    .hero,
    .story-picker,
    .story-head,
    .story-body {
      padding: 0.9rem;
    }

    .story-body p {
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    .story-body--with-aside-image {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .story-body--with-aside-image .story-image--aside {
      grid-column: 1;
      grid-row: auto;
      position: static;
      max-width: none;
    }

    .story-body--with-aside-image .story-image-button--aside {
      grid-column: 1;
      grid-row: auto;
      position: static;
      max-width: none;
    }

    .story-body--with-aside-image p {
      grid-column: 1;
    }

    .story-image--aside {
      width: 100%;
      margin: 0 0 0.85rem;
    }

    .story-toolbar {
      align-items: stretch;
    }

    .story-switcher {
      width: 100%;
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: flex-start;
    }

    .story-switcher select {
      width: 100%;
      min-width: 0;
    }
  }
</style>
